---

This repository vendors third-party components that retain their own licenses
and copyright notices; this MIT license does not supersede them:

  - Adafruit CircuitPython libraries under src/lib/ (the compiled .mpy bundle:
    adafruit_requests, adafruit_matrixportal, adafruit_display_text,
    adafruit_httpserver, asyncio, neopixel, and their dependencies) — copyright
    Adafruit Industries and contributors, MIT License. These are redistributed
    unmodified so the device has its runtime dependencies on board.

  - src/fonts/tom-thumb.bdf — the Tom Thumb 4×6 monospace bitmap font by Robey
    Pointer, released as free for any use (public-domain-style).

  - src/fonts/Teeny-Tiny-Pixls-5.bdf and src/fonts/teeny-tiny-pixls-font/ —
    "Teeny Tiny Pixls" by Chequered Ink Ltd. Free for all use; per its bundled
    license the font file itself may not be redistributed without permission
    from Chequered Ink Ltd. See src/fonts/teeny-tiny-pixls-font/misc/License.txt.

ThemeParkWaits runs on the separate ScrollKit library
(https://github.com/czei/scrollkit), which is not vendored in this repository
and is independently licensed under the MIT License by the same author.

Live wait-time and park data are provided by the themeparks.wiki API
(https://themeparks.wiki). The application displays "ThemeParks.wiki"
attribution on the device as required; the data itself is not part of this
Software and is subject to that project's terms.
